{"lemma":"ضابِطُ","slug":"ضابِطُ","root":"ض.ب.ط","root_slug":"ض-ب-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ب-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25502"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B7%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"officer"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tenant farmer or villein","tags":["Iraq","dialectal"],"examples":[{"text":"Comme le choix des zabets ou fermiers depend entièrement du caprice du propriétaire, la durée de la location dépend aussi de sa volontée, et elle cesse aussitôt que le fermier qu’il a choisi ne le satisfait pas par l’exactitude des payemens, soit en denrées, soit en argent.","english":"Like the choice of ḍubbāt (note: one transcribes the better-known “officer” meaning alike in French) entirely depends on the caprice of the owner, the durity of the location also depends on his will, and it passes as early as the farmer which he has chosen does not satisfy the exaction of payments, be it in kind or be it in money."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reglement, regulation, custom, usage"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pair of compasses","tags":["obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"البركار بالراء هو الضابط عن أبي الفتوح، قرأتُ في إصلاح المنطق للدينوري: والبرجار يقال إنّه البركار.","english":"Birkār with r is pair of compasses after Abū al-Futūḥ, and I have read in the Improvement of Speech of Ad-Dīnawarī that birjār is birkār."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of ضَبَطَ (ḍabaṭa, “to regulate etc.”)."},"ipa":["/dˤaː.bitˤ/","/ðaː.bitˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25502","headword_ar":"ضَابِطٌ","root":"DbT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keeping, preserving, guarding, maintaining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking care of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with prudence, precaution,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good judgment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"effectually:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1:) and hence,] (assumed tropical:)  one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who manages his affairs with prudence, precaution,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good judgment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soundly, taking the sure course therein, and exercising caution,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"care, that they may not become beyond his power of management:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keeping to"},{"kind":"text","text":"anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inseparably,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constantly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see, again, 1:)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking, holding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retaining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strongly, vehemently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firmly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabanoTFY","text_ar":"ضَبَنْطًى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IDrd:) or the latter of these, (S,) which is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabanoTFuY","text_ar":"حَبَنْطًُى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, [in some copies of the K erroneously written without tenween,]) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"being augmentative, to render the word quasi-coordinate to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarojalN","text_ar":"سَفَرْجَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or both; applied to a man and to a camel; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"powerful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or [a man]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great in might,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"valour, and power, and body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) and the former, a camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong to work"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"labour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner, applied to a man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAbiTu","text_ar":"ضَابِطُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^umuwri","text_ar":"الاُمُورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the strong"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and resolute"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firm-minded"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the performance"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"management of affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDobaTu","text_ar":"اَضْبَطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [It often signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Exact; correct;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accurate;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHaq~iqN","text_ar":"مُحَقِّقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with which it is said to be syn. in Har p. 254;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honest;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faithful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly as applied to an author or a relater.]       -A2-  As a conventional term,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAbiTN","text_ar":"ضَابِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qEd","text_ar":"قعد"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAbiTapN","text_ar":"ضَابِطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DawaAbiTu","text_ar":"ضَوَابِطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAEidapN","text_ar":"قَاعِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) signifying (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A universal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"general, rule,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DAbT","text_ar":"ضابط"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that comprises subdivisions of one class only;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whereas a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qAEdp","text_ar":"قاعدة"},{"kind":"text","text":"comprises [sometimes] subdivisions of various classes. (Kull, p. 290.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","IDrd","K","T","Msb"]}]}}